name: Ecwid
description: Add an Ecwid Instance to connect your existing Ecwid account to the eCommerce Hub, allowing you to manage orders and products across multiple eCommerce Elements. You will need your Ecwid account information to add an instance.
configDescription: If you do not have an Ecwid account, you can create one at Ecwid Signup

configuration.name: OAuth Scope
configuration.defaultValue: read_store_profile update_store_profile create_orders update_orders read_orders create_catalog update_catalog read_catalog update_discount_coupons create_discount_coupons read_discount_coupons create_customers update_customers read_customers

configuration.name: Authentication Type
configuration.description: For User Access Token select 'oauth2' and for App Access Token select 'custom'

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Event Notification Subscription ID
configuration.description: The subscription ID for the webhook events subscription

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event Notification Callback URL
configuration.description: An application callback URL used for event notifications from box and Cloud Elements, e.g., Uploaded Files, etc.

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

resources.description: Find customers in the eCommerce system, using the provided CEQL search expression. If no search expression is provided, all records will be retrieved

parameters.name: where
parameters.description:
The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query (i.e. field='value').

Supported search terms: customer_id and customer_email. All other search criteria are ignored. NOTE: When searching by customer_id, do not quote the value (ex: customer_id=15693430), as the ID is a number rather than a string. When searching by email, quote the value (ex: customer_email='a@b.c'), as the email parameter is a string

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page number. When this parameter is omitted, 1 is implied

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The number of results to fetch in a given page. When this parameter is omitted, a maximum of 200 results are returned

resources.description:
Update a product associated with a given ID in the eCommerce system. The update API uses the PATCH HTTP verb, so only those fields provided in the product object will be updated, and those fields not provided will be left alone. Updating a product with a specified ID that does not exist will result in an error response.

Update supports the following fields: sku, quantity, trackQuantity, quantityDelta, warningLimit, name, price, weight, tangible, enabled, fixedShippingRateOnly, fixedShippingRate, description, wholesalePrices, compareAtPrice, productClassId

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the product to update in the eCommerce system

parameters.name: product
parameters.description: The product object, with those fields that are to be updated

enabled.description: true if the category is enabled, false otherwise

compareAtPrice.description: Products sale price displayed strike-out in the customer

productClassId.description: Id of the product type that this product belongs to.

quantity.description: Amount of product items in stock.
